    • addDuration

      public void addDuration(ReconciliationStatistic.DurationMetric metric, long startNanoTime)
      For the given key, calculates and records the time-duration, since startNanoTime occurred in the current thread.

      Calling thread must be the same thread used to call DurationStatistics.startNanoTime().

      Parameters:
      metric - Metric for statistic
      startNanoTime - Start-time, in nanoseconds

    • processed

      public void processed(String sourceId, String targetId, boolean linkExisted, String linkId, boolean linkWasCreated, org.forgerock.openidm.sync.impl.Situation situation, ReconAction action)
      Handle the processed notification to update the statistics appropriately
      Parameters:
      sourceId - The source id processed, or null if none
      targetId - The target id processed, or null if none
      linkExisted - indication if the link existed before the operation
      linkId - the link identifier, if available. For created links this may not currently be available.
      linkWasCreated - indication if a new link was created during the operation
      situation - the assessed situation
      action - the action that was processed
